Suggestion: Implement a Maximum Number of Iterations
One possible fix is to implement a maximum number of iterations for the algorithm, in addition to the maximum number of evaluations. This would prevent the algorithm from entering an infinite loop and exceeding the maximum allowed number of evaluations. The modified code would be:
```java
// Add a maximum number of iterations
private static final int MAX_ITERATIONS = 100;

// ...

// Keep finding better approximations.
int iterations = 0;
while (true) {
    // ...

    // Check if the maximum number of iterations has been reached
    if (iterations >= MAX_ITERATIONS) {
        throw new ConvergenceException();
    }

    iterations++;
}
```
